# templates/core/github/CODEOWNERS.template
# Sourcing mode: pattern-only (per specs/00-vision-and-license.md §"Sourcing modes")
# Routes Claude config + governance docs to the repo owner so they're
# notified on every change. The owner can be a GitHub user (`@octocat`)
# or a team (`@org/security`).
#
# When you adopt this template, save it as `<consumer>/.github/CODEOWNERS`
# (strip the `.template` suffix; no extension) and search-and-replace
# `{{REPO_OWNER}}` with your owner handle.
#
# See https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Authored: 2026-05-12
# License: CC0 1.0 (templates ship CC0 per specs/00-vision-and-license.md §"License")

# Claude Code per-project config — any change here affects how every
# Claude session in this repo behaves; reviewer should be the same
# person who maintains the kit-level config.
.claude/         @{{REPO_OWNER}}
.mcp.json        @{{REPO_OWNER}}

# Project memory and onboarding — load-bearing docs every Claude session
# reads on start.
CLAUDE.md        @{{REPO_OWNER}}
ONBOARDING.md    @{{REPO_OWNER}}

# Compliance docs — jurisdiction/regulator-specific content. A single
# reviewer keeps voice + accuracy consistent.
docs/compliance/ @{{REPO_OWNER}}
